[normal]2)[bold]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Resilience[bold]a)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Lincolnshire, like most authorities, is prepared for and copes with severe winter weather as d
[normal]emonstrated during the winter of 2012/2013.  However an extreme winter event on the scale of 1963
[normal],
[normal] with its prolonged low temperatures and heavy snowfall
[normal],
[normal] would 
[normal]cause massive disruption especially to food distribution 
[normal]especially 
[normal]due
[normal] to "just in time" stock
[normal] distribution.
[normal]b)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Lincolnsh
[normal]ire continues to be heavily inv
[normal]olved in nationally implementing the 
[normal]Quarmby
[normal] Review by its chairmanship of the 
[normal]National Winter Service Research Group (
[normal]NWSRG
[normal])
[normal].
[normal]i)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Following recommendations contained within the 
[normal]Quarmby
[normal] Review the 
[normal]NWSRG ha
[normal]s become a sub group of the 
[normal]UK Roads Board (
[normal]UKR
[normal]B)
[normal]ii)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Through its chairmanship of the NWSRG Lincolnshire has instigate
[normal]d
[normal] a fundamental review of
[normal] national
[normal] highway winter
[normal] maintenance practices which
[normal] has resulted in 
[normal]the 
[normal]implementation of 
[normal]a 
