[normal]What lessons have been learned since the winter of 2009-[bold]2010?[bold]a)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]A major learning point has been a realisation by the public and industry 
[normal]al
[normal]ike 
[normal]that l
[normal]ocal 
[normal]highway 
[normal]authorities cannot do everything on their own in time
[normal]s
[normal] of severe winter weather and 
[normal]that 
[normal]they need community help.  
[normal]i)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Lincolnshire has engaged with all tiers of local government from District Authorities, Parish Councils and Community Groups.  
[normal]ii)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]All these groups have been encouraged to engage with Lincolnshire County Council on mutual aid and self-help arrangements
[normal], althou
[normal]gh there has only been a 25% take up by Parish Councils to this process
[normal].
[normal]iii)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Public engagement has been encouraged especially on snow clearance of carriageways and footways following clarity on the legal situation contained within the 
[normal]Quarmby
[normal] Review.
[normal]iv)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Mutual ai
[normal]d arrangements are also in place with all the main hospitals in the county including accident and emergency centres.
[normal]b)
